<http://dx.doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4350.2.6>
    bibo:endPage "316" ;
    bibo:issue "2" ;
    bibo:journal "Zootaxa" ;
    bibo:pubDate "2017-11-17" ;
    bibo:startPage "301" ;
    bibo:volume "4350" ;
    dc:creator "Chávez, Germán; Catenazzi, Alessandro; Venegas, Pablo J." ;
    dc:date "2017" ;
    dc:title "A new species of arboreal microteiid lizard of the genus Euspondylus (Gymnophtalmidae: Cercosaurinae) from the Andean slopes of central Peru with comments on Peruvian Euspondylus" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1053172>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1053178>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1053180>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1053174>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1053176>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1053182>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1053184> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1053172>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Views of the holotype (CORBIDI 16457; SVL = 69.4 mm); A) coloration in life; B) dorsal view of the coloration in preservative; C) ventral view of the coloration in preservative. Photographs by Lesly Luján (A), and Germán Chávez (B, C)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1053172/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1053178>
    dc:description "FIGURE 5. Dorsal views of the head of species of Euspondylus, showing the condition of the first supraocular and first superciliar, pointed with red arrows: A) Euspondylus guentheri (BMNH 1946.8.8.99); B) Euspondylus maculatus (MHNN 2105 - 1); C) Euspondylus excelsum sp. nov. (CORBIDI 16457); D) Euspondylus sp 1 (FMNH 45474); E) Euspondylus sp 2 (AMNH 1704). Photographs by Patrick Campbell (A), Alessandro Catenazzi (B, D, E), and Lesly Luján (C)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1053178/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1053180>
    dc:description "FIGURE 6. Views of the hemipenes of the holotype of Euspondylus excelsum sp. nov., A) ventral or sulcate side; B) lateral side; C) dorsal or asulcate side. Photographs by Germán Chávez." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1053180/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1053174>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Views of the dorsum (left) and venter (right) of the paratypes in life, A – B) Adult male (CORBIDI 16465, SVL = 83.7 mm); C – D) Adult female (CORBIDI 16463, SVL = 81.4); E – F) Juvenile male (CORBIDI 16468, SVL = 47.7). Photographs by Lesly Luján." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1053174/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1053176>
    dc:description "FIGURE 4. Sexual dimorphism in Euspondylus excelsum sp. nov., A) ventral view of the tail of a male (CORBIDI 16465) showing black blotches on the entire surface; B) Close up of the ventral side of the thigh of an adult male (CORBIDI 16465) showing the femoral pores (pointed with red arrows); C) ventral view of the tail of a female (CORBIDI 16463) showing black blotches arranged dorsolaterally; D) Close up of the ventral side of the thigh of an adult female (CORBIDI 16463) showing the absence of femoral pores. Photographs by Germán Chávez." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1053176/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1053182>
    dc:description "FIGURE 7. Condition of the habitat of Euspondylus excelsum sp. nov., A – B) foothills forests flooded by an hydroelectric project, only with the canopy protruding from the water; C) Individual (pointed with a red arrow) perched on a leaf at the level of water surface in a flooded forest; D) Bromeliad inhabited by an individual of E. excelsum as a shelter. Photographs by Lesly Luján." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1053182/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1053184>
    dc:description "FIGURE 8. Type locality (yellow star) and localities for the paratypes (yellow triangle) of Euspondylus excelsum sp. nov.; type locality of E. maculatus (green circle); Chanchamayo, Junin department (blue circle), where specimens of Euspondylus sp. 1 were collected, and Inca Mine, Puno department (red circle) where Euspondylus sp. 2 was collected. Map by Caterina H. Cosmópolis." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1053184/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

